h3. Problem Definition
Currently *isCumulative=false* is no longer used in created vs resolved chart in JIRA as this is replaced with *operation=cumulative*.

The chart still stores the parameter for *isCumulative=false* which caused report generated by [PDF View Plugin for JIRA (PDF Exporter)|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.midori.jira.plugin.pdfview/server/overview] not to be cumulative.

h3. Suggested Solution
Remove *isCumulative=false* parameter from *created vs resolved chart* since now the used parameter for cumulative is *operation=cumulative*.

h3. Why this is important
If user is using [PDF View Plugin for JIRA (PDF Exporter)|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.midori.jira.plugin.pdfview/server/overview] to extract report as pdf the are not getting correct result due to the fact that the parameter supplied by the gadget to the plugin includes *isCumulative=false* as shown below{code}
User prefs: {isConfigured=true, isPopup=false, refresh=false, periodName=monthly, showUnresolvedTrend=false, projectOrFilterId=,
type=project, versionLabel=major, isCumulative=false, name=Timezone, daysprevious=200, id=10200, operation=cumulative}
{code}
 
h3. Workaround 
No workaround is available at the moment

